    "It is worth noting that GNNs may also be derived using a GDL perspective if we set the symmetry group G to S jV j, the permutation group of jVj objects.",
    "Owing to the design of Eq.",
    "(2), its outputs will not be dependent on the exact permutation of nodes in the input graph.",
    "A simple mechanism to enforce G-invariance, given any predictor f G ðX, E, gÞ, performs frame averaging across all G-transformed inputs:",
    "This ensures that all G-transformed versions of a particular input (also known as that input's orbit) will have exactly the same output, satisfying Eq."
